<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Powerful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Powerful,</orth> 1) strong, mighty, forcible: <cit><quote>this p. rhyme,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 55.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 55, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this p. might,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.150.1" default="NO" valid="yes">150, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O p. love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 4</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. to araise King Pepin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his p. sound,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 79</bibl></cit> <emph>'tis p.</emph> (the planet) <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 202</bibl>. <cit><quote>you're p. at it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 28</bibl></cit> (you are a master in it). <cit><quote>gallows and knock are too p. on the highway,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 29</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. policy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 58</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>winter's p. wind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 15</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with a broad and p. fan,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. grace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 3, 15</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a charm of p. trouble,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>drawn by the p. sun,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 169</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>mixtures p. o'er the blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 104</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy p. breath,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 78</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) having great authority or command: <cit><quote>some p. spirit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 186</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all their p. friends,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 55</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the p. regions under earth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his p. arm,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.223" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 223</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his p. mandate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 1, 22</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>